<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-08-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-08-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="40" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d40">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/2078</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                President <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-30">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 30, 1915</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. President</hi>: You have undoubtedly
                            read the flimsy of Mr. Page’s 2716, August 29, two p. m.<note n="9" xml:id="d40fn1">
                                <ref target="frus1915Supp#pg_528">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 528</ref>.</note> relative to
                            the attack on the <hi rend="italic">Nicosian</hi> and the events which
                            followed. To me the conduct of the British naval authorities is
                            shocking, and I sincerely hope that this matter may not become public,
                            as it would seriously affect public opinion in Germany and might result
                            in retaliatory measures of a most rigorous character.</p>
                        <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>